parg
------------------------------------------
Header only c++ library for parsing command line arguments and generating
usage/help output

Runtime requirements:

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  binutils-2.29-1
  cmake-3.13.1-1
  cygport-0.33.1-1
  gcc-core-7.4.0-1
  gcc-g++-7.4.0-1

Canonical website:
  https://github.com/octobanana/parg

Canonical download:
  https://github.com/octobanana/parg/archive/v0.2.0.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack parg-0.2.0-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./parg-0.2.0-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/parg-0.2.0-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/parg-0.2.0-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(parg)
  /usr/include/ob/parg.hh
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/parg.README
  /usr/share/doc/parg/LICENSE
  /usr/share/doc/parg/README.md

------------------

